  "prompt": "What are the all time best hollywood movies?",
  "response": "Determining the \"all-time best\" Hollywood movies can be subjective, as it often depends on individual taste, cultural impact, and various other factors. However, several films are frequently cited as some of the best in Hollywood history. Here\u2019s a list that includes a mix of critically acclaimed films, influential classics, and popular favorites:\n\n### Classic Films\n1. **Citizen Kane** (1941) - Directed by Orson Welles\n2. **Casablanca** (1942) - Directed by Michael Curtiz\n3. **Gone with the Wind** (1939) - Directed by Victor Fleming\n4. **The Wizard of Oz** (1939) - Directed by Victor Fleming\n5. **Psycho** (1960) - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock\n\n### Iconic Dramas\n6. **The Godfather** (1972) - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola\n7. **Schindler's List** (1993) - Directed by Steven Spielberg\n8. **12 Angry Men** (1957) - Directed by Sidney Lumet\n9. **One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest** (1975) - Directed by Milo\u0161 Forman\n10. **Forrest Gump** (1994) - Directed by Robert Zemeckis\n\n### Groundbreaking Sci-Fi & Fantasy\n11. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope** (1977) - Directed by George Lucas\n12. **2001: A Space Odyssey** (1968) - Directed by Stanley Kubrick\n13. **The Matrix** (1999) - Directed by The Wachowskis\n14. **Jurassic Park** (1993) - Directed by Steven Spielberg\n15. **Inception** (2010) - Directed by Christopher Nolan\n\n### Beloved Comedies\n16. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) - Directed by Billy Wilder\n17. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail** (1975) - Directed by Terry Gilliam and Terry Jones\n18. **Groundhog Day** (1993) - Directed by Harold Ramis\n19. **The Big Lebowski** (1998) - Directed by the Coen Brothers\n20. **Superbad** (2007) - Directed by Greg Mottola\n\n### Contemporary Masterpieces\n21. **Pulp Fiction** (1994) - Directed by Quentin Tarantino\n22. **The Shawshank Redemption** (1994) - Directed by Frank Darabont\n23. **Fight Club** (1999) - Directed by David Fincher\n24. **The Social Network** (2010) - Directed by David Fincher\n25. **Mad Max: Fury Road** (2015) - Directed by George Miller\n\n### Animation and Family\n26. **Toy Story** (1995) - Directed by John Lasseter\n27. **The Lion King** (1994) - Directed by Roger Allers and Rob Minkoff\n28. **Spirited Away** (2001) - Directed by Hayao Miyazaki (although it is technically a Japanese film, it was widely distributed in the U.S.)\n29. **Finding Nemo** (2003) - Directed by Andrew Stanton\n30. **Shrek** (2001) - Directed by Andrew Adamson and Vicky Jenson\n\n### Notable Mentions\n31. **The Silence of the Lambs** (1991) - Directed by Jonathan Demme\n32. **The Departed** (2006) - Directed by Martin Scorsese\n33. **Chinatown** (1974) - Directed by Roman Polanski\n34. **Saving Private Ryan** (1998) - Directed by Steven Spielberg\n35. **Gladiator** (2000) - Directed by Ridley Scott\n\nThis is by no means an exhaustive list, and many other films could easily be included based on various criteria. However, these movies have achieved significant acclaim and recognition in both critical and popular circles.",
